pcubeSeMIB.name: pcubeSeMIB

revisions.description: - Increased the supported range of global controllers (globalControllersIndex) from (1..255) to (1..2147483647) - Improved counter descriptions to reflect the counted layer for the following byte and bandwidth counters: txQueuesBandwidth txQueuesDroppedBytes globalControllersBandwidth globalControllersDroppedBytes

MIB revised as a part of integration into Cisco SNMP MIB standard, main changes: changed contaces, added OBJECT-GROUPs, added MODULE-COMPLIANCE, renamed with a prefix 'p' the following tables/objects to avoid conflict with existing Cisco MIbs: moduleGrp, moduleTable, moduleIndex, moduleType, moduleNumTrafficProcessors, moduleSlotNum, moduleHwVersion, moduleNumPorts, moduleNumLinks, moduleConnectionMode, moduleSerialNumber, moduleUpStreamAttackFilteringTime, moduleUpStreamLastAttackFilteringTime, moduleDownStreamAttackFilteringTime, moduleDownStreamLastAttackFilteringTime, moduleAttackObjectsClearTime , moduleAdminStatus, moduleOperStatus, chassisGrp chassisSysType, chassisPowerSupplyAlarm, chassisFansAlarm, chassisTempAlarm, chassisVoltageAlarm, chassisNumSlots, chassisSlotConfig, chassisPsuType, chassisLineFeedAlarm, portGrp, portTable, portModuleIndex, portIndex, portType, portNumTxQueues, portIfIndex, portAdminSpeed, portAdminDuplex, portOperDuplex, portLinkIndex, portOperStatus removed attackTypeTableClearTime counter, renamed Pcube to Cisco and SE to SCE.
Updates of OS version 3.0.3: added mplsVpnAutoLearning group containing mplsVpnSoftwareCountersTable and added mplsVpnTotalHWMappingsThresholdExceededTrap.
Updates of OS version 3.0.0: added vas group containing vasServerTable and added vasServerOpertionalStatusChangeTrap.

Updates of OS version 2.5.5: added rdrFormatterCategoryNumReportsQueued to the rdrFormatterCategoryTable in the RDR-formatter group, added subscribersNumAnonymous and subscribersNumWithSessions to subscriber info,Added the group attackGrp, containing attackTypeTable.

Updates of OS version 2.5: added tpServiceLoss to traffic processor group, added droppedBytes to Tx-Queue and global controller, added TpIpRanges to subscriber info,deprecated telnetSession* traps, replaced by session* traps.
Updates of OS version 1.5: added entries to the tpTable, added entries to the rdrFormatterGrp and rdrFormatterDestTable,added entries to the portTable and attack filter traps.

pcubeSeMIB.description: Main SNMP MIB for Cisco's SCE OS products such as SCE2000 and SE100. This MIB provides configuration and runtime status for chassis, control modules, and line modules on the SCOS systems.

LinkModeType.name: LinkModeType
LinkModeType.description: The various modes of a link.

sysOperationalStatus.name: sysOperationalStatus
sysOperationalStatus.description: Indicates the operational status of the system.

sysFailureRecovery.name: sysFailureRecovery
sysFailureRecovery.description: Indicates if the system should enter a Failure mode after abnormal boot.

pchassisPowerSupplyAlarm.name: pchassisPowerSupplyAlarm
pchassisPowerSupplyAlarm.description: Indicates if the power supply to the chassis is normal. If the status is not 'ok' it means that one or more power supplies are not functional.

pchassisFansAlarm.name: pchassisFansAlarm
pchassisFansAlarm.description: Indicates if all the fans on the chassis are functional.

pchassisVoltageAlarm.name: pchassisVoltageAlarm
pchassisVoltageAlarm.description: The chassis internal voltage alarm status. If the alarm is 'on' it indicates that the voltage level of one or more HW units is not in the normal range.

pchassisNumSlots.name: pchassisNumSlots
pchassisNumSlots.description: Indicates the number of slots in the chassis available for plug-in modules. This number counts slots that are already occupied as well as empty slots.

pchassisSlotConfig.name: pchassisSlotConfig
pchassisSlotConfig.description: An indication of which slots in the chassis have modules inserted. This is an integer value with bits set to indicate configured modules. It can be interpreted as a sum of f(x) as x goes from 1 to the number of slots, where f(x) = 0 for no module inserted and f(x) = exp(2, x-1) for a module inserted.

pchassisPsuType.name: pchassisPsuType
pchassisPsuType.description: Indicates the type of the power supplies.

pchassisLineFeedAlarm.name: pchassisLineFeedAlarm
pchassisLineFeedAlarm.description: Indicates if the line feed to the chassis is normal. If the status is not 'ok' it means that one or more line feeds are not connected or have no power.

pmoduleTable.name: pmoduleTable
pmoduleTable.description: A list of module entries. The number of entries is the number of modules in the chassis.

pmoduleEntry.name: pmoduleEntry
pmoduleEntry.description: Entry containing information about one module in the chassis.

pmoduleIndex.name: pmoduleIndex
pmoduleIndex.description: A unique value for each module within the chassis.

pmoduleNumTrafficProcessors.name: pmoduleNumTrafficProcessors
pmoduleNumTrafficProcessors.description: The number of traffic processors supported by this module.

pmoduleSlotNum.name: pmoduleSlotNum
pmoduleSlotNum.description: This value is determined by the chassis slot number where this module is located. Valid entries are 1 to the value of chassisNumSlots.

pmoduleHwVersion.name: pmoduleHwVersion
pmoduleHwVersion.description: The hardware version of the module.

pmoduleNumPorts.name: pmoduleNumPorts
pmoduleNumPorts.description: The number of ports supported by this module.

pmoduleNumLinks.name: pmoduleNumLinks
pmoduleNumLinks.description: The number of links carrying inband traffic that are supported by this module. Link is uniquely defined by the two ports that are at its end-points.

pmoduleConnectionMode.name: pmoduleConnectionMode
pmoduleConnectionMode.description: Indicates the connection mode of a module.

pmoduleSerialNumber.name: pmoduleSerialNumber
pmoduleSerialNumber.description: Indicates the serial number of the module.

pmoduleUpStreamAttackFilteringTime.name: pmoduleUpStreamAttackFilteringTime
pmoduleUpStreamAttackFilteringTime.description: Indicates the accumulated time which attack up-stream traffic was filtered.

pmoduleUpStreamLastAttackFilteringTime.name: pmoduleUpStreamLastAttackFilteringTime
pmoduleUpStreamLastAttackFilteringTime.description: Indicates the time since the previous attack was filtered in the up-stream traffic.

pmoduleDownStreamAttackFilteringTime.name: pmoduleDownStreamAttackFilteringTime
pmoduleDownStreamAttackFilteringTime.description: Indicates the accumulated time which attack down-stream traffic was filtered.

pmoduleDownStreamLastAttackFilteringTime.name: pmoduleDownStreamLastAttackFilteringTime
pmoduleDownStreamLastAttackFilteringTime.description: Indicates the time since the previous attack was filtered in the down-stream traffic.

pmoduleAttackObjectsClearTime.name: pmoduleAttackObjectsClearTime
pmoduleAttackObjectsClearTime.description: Indicates the time since the attack objects were cleared. Writing a 0 to this object causes the counters to be cleared.

pmoduleAdminStatus.name: pmoduleAdminStatus
pmoduleAdminStatus.description: Indicates configuration of a module in respect to whether the module should handle traffic.

pmoduleOperStatus.name: pmoduleOperStatus
pmoduleOperStatus.description: Indicates current module's role in respect to whether the module handles traffic.

linkTable.name: linkTable
linkTable.description: The Link table provides information regarding the configuration and status of the links that pass through the SE and carry inband traffic. The number of entries in this table is determined by the number of modules in the chassis and the number of links on each module.

linkEntry.name: linkEntry
linkEntry.description: Entry containing information about the Link.

linkModuleIndex.name: linkModuleIndex
linkModuleIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies the module where this link is located.

linkIndex.name: linkIndex
linkIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies this link within a module. Valid entries are 1 to the value of moduleNumLinks for this module.

linkAdminModeOnActive.name: linkAdminModeOnActive
linkAdminModeOnActive.description: The desired mode of the link when the module's operating status is Active and the module is not in boot or failure. The possible modes are bypass, forwarding and sniffing. In bypass mode the traffic is forwarded from one port to the other using an internal splitter. In forwarding mode the traffic is forwarded through the internal hardware and software modules of the SE. In sniffing mode the traffic is passed in the same manner as in bypass mode, however a copy of the traffic is made and analyzed internally in the box.

linkAdminModeOnFailure.name: linkAdminModeOnFailure
linkAdminModeOnFailure.description: The desired mode of the link when the system's operational status is Failure. The possible modes are Bypass and Cutoff. In Bypass mode the traffic is forwarded from one port to the other using an internal splitter. In Cutoff mode the traffic is dropped by the SE.

linkOperMode.name: linkOperMode
linkOperMode.description: The operational mode of the link. In Bypass mode the traffic is forwarded from one port to the other using an internal splitter. In Forwarding mode the traffic is forwarded through the internal software and hardware modules of the SCE. In Sniffing mode the traffic is forwarded in the same manner as in Bypass mode, however the traffic is passed through the internal software and hardware modules of the SCE for analyzing. in Cutoff mode the traffic is dropped by the SCE platform.

linkStatusReflectionEnable.name: linkStatusReflectionEnable
linkStatusReflectionEnable.description: Indicates if failure of the physical link on one i/f should trigger the failure of the link on the other i/f.

linkSubscriberSidePortIndex.name: linkSubscriberSidePortIndex
linkSubscriberSidePortIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies this link with its related port that is connected to the subscriber side.

linkNetworkSidePortIndex.name: linkNetworkSidePortIndex
linkNetworkSidePortIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies this link with its related port that is connected to the network side.

rdrFormatterEnable.name: rdrFormatterEnable
rdrFormatterEnable.description: Indicates whether the RDR-formatter is enabled or disabled. When the RDR-formatter is enabled, it sends the reports it gets from the traffic processors to the Data Collector as defined in the rdrFormatterDestTable.

rdrFormatterDestTable.name: rdrFormatterDestTable
rdrFormatterDestTable.description: The RDR-formatter destinations table (0 to 3 entries). This table lists the addresses of Data Collectors. If the RDR-formatter is enabled, the destination with the highest priority that a TCP connection to it can be established would receive the reports generated by the traffic processors.

rdrFormatterDestIPAddr.name: rdrFormatterDestIPAddr
rdrFormatterDestIPAddr.description: The IP address of a Data Collector.

rdrFormatterDestPort.name: rdrFormatterDestPort
rdrFormatterDestPort.description: The TCP port on which the Data Collector listens.

rdrFormatterDestPriority.name: rdrFormatterDestPriority
rdrFormatterDestPriority.description: The priority given to the Data Collector. The active Data Collector is the Data Collector with the highest priority and a TCP connection that is up.

rdrFormatterDestStatus.name: rdrFormatterDestStatus
rdrFormatterDestStatus.description: In 'redundancy(2)' and in 'simpleLoadBalancing(3)' rdrFormatterForwardingMode there can be only one 'active' destination, which is where the reports are currently being sent to. In 'multicast(4)' modes all destinations will receive the active(2) status.

rdrFormatterDestConnectionStatus.name: rdrFormatterDestConnectionStatus
rdrFormatterDestConnectionStatus.description: Indicates the status of TCP connection to this destination.

rdrFormatterDestNumReportsSent.name: rdrFormatterDestNumReportsSent
rdrFormatterDestNumReportsSent.description: Indicates the number of reports sent by the RDR-formatter to this destination.

rdrFormatterDestNumReportsDiscarded.name: rdrFormatterDestNumReportsDiscarded
rdrFormatterDestNumReportsDiscarded.description: Indicates the number of reports dropped by the RDR-formatter on this destination.

rdrFormatterDestReportRate.name: rdrFormatterDestReportRate
rdrFormatterDestReportRate.description: Indicates the rate of the reports (in reports per second) currently sent to this destination.

rdrFormatterDestReportRatePeak.name: rdrFormatterDestReportRatePeak
rdrFormatterDestReportRatePeak.description: Indicates the maximum report rate sent to this destination.

rdrFormatterDestReportRatePeakTime.name: rdrFormatterDestReportRatePeakTime
rdrFormatterDestReportRatePeakTime.description: Indicates the time since the rdrFormatterDestReportRatePeak value occurred.

rdrFormatterNumReportsSent.name: rdrFormatterNumReportsSent
rdrFormatterNumReportsSent.description: Indicates the number of reports sent by the RDR-formatter.

rdrFormatterNumReportsDiscarded.name: rdrFormatterNumReportsDiscarded
rdrFormatterNumReportsDiscarded.description: Indicates the number of reports dropped by the RDR-formatter.

rdrFormatterClearCountersTime.name: rdrFormatterClearCountersTime
rdrFormatterClearCountersTime.description: The time since RDR-formatter counters were last cleared. Writing a 0 to this object causes the RDR-formatter counters to be cleared.

rdrFormatterReportRate.name: rdrFormatterReportRate
rdrFormatterReportRate.description: Indicates the rate of the reports (in reports per second) currently sent to all of the destinations.

rdrFormatterReportRatePeak.name: rdrFormatterReportRatePeak
rdrFormatterReportRatePeak.description: Indicates the maximum report rate sent to all of the destinations.

rdrFormatterReportRatePeakTime.name: rdrFormatterReportRatePeakTime
rdrFormatterReportRatePeakTime.description: Indicates the time since the rdrFormatterReportRatePeak value occurred.

rdrFormatterProtocol.name: rdrFormatterProtocol
rdrFormatterProtocol.description: Indicates the RDR protocol currently in use.

rdrFormatterForwardingMode.name: rdrFormatterForwardingMode
rdrFormatterForwardingMode.description: Indicates the mode of how the RDR formatter sends the reports to its destinations.

rdrFormatterCategoryTable.name: rdrFormatterCategoryTable
rdrFormatterCategoryTable.description: The RDR-formatter Category table. Describes the different categories of RDRs and RDR destination groups.

rdrFormatterCategoryName.name: rdrFormatterCategoryName
rdrFormatterCategoryName.description: The name given to this category.

rdrFormatterCategoryNumReportsSent.name: rdrFormatterCategoryNumReportsSent
rdrFormatterCategoryNumReportsSent.description: Indicates the number of reports sent by the RDR-formatter to this category.

rdrFormatterCategoryNumReportsDiscarded.name: rdrFormatterCategoryNumReportsDiscarded
rdrFormatterCategoryNumReportsDiscarded.description: Indicates the number of reports dropped by the RDR-formatter on this category.

rdrFormatterCategoryReportRate.name: rdrFormatterCategoryReportRate
rdrFormatterCategoryReportRate.description: Indicates the rate of the reports (in reports per second) currently sent to this category.

rdrFormatterCategoryReportRatePeak.name: rdrFormatterCategoryReportRatePeak
rdrFormatterCategoryReportRatePeak.description: Indicates the maximum report rate sent to this category.

rdrFormatterCategoryReportRatePeakTime.name: rdrFormatterCategoryReportRatePeakTime
rdrFormatterCategoryReportRatePeakTime.description: Indicates the time since the rdrFormatterCategoryReportRatePeak value occurred.

rdrFormatterCategoryNumReportsQueued.name: rdrFormatterCategoryNumReportsQueued
rdrFormatterCategoryNumReportsQueued.description: Indicates the amount of pending reports in this category.

rdrFormatterCategoryDestTable.name: rdrFormatterCategoryDestTable
rdrFormatterCategoryDestTable.description: The RDR-formatter Category destinations table. This table lists the addresses of Data Collectors. If the RDR-formatter is enabled, the destination with the highest priority that a TCP connection to it can be established would receive the reports generated by the traffic processors.

rdrFormatterCategoryDestPriority.name: rdrFormatterCategoryDestPriority
rdrFormatterCategoryDestPriority.description: The priority given to the Data Collector for this category. The active Data Collector is the Data Collector with the highest priority and a TCP connection that is up.

rdrFormatterCategoryDestStatus.name: rdrFormatterCategoryDestStatus
rdrFormatterCategoryDestStatus.description: In modes 'redundancy(2)' and in 'simpleLoadBalancing(3)' there can be only one 'active' destination, which is the destination to which reports are being sent. In 'multicast(4)' modes all destination will receive the 'active(2)' status.

loggerUserLogEnable.name: loggerUserLogEnable
loggerUserLogEnable.description: Indicates whether the logging of user information is enabled or disabled.

loggerUserLogNumInfo.name: loggerUserLogNumInfo
loggerUserLogNumInfo.description: Indicates the number of Info messages logged into the user log file since last reboot or last time the counter was cleared.

loggerUserLogNumWarning.name: loggerUserLogNumWarning
loggerUserLogNumWarning.description: Indicates the number of Warning messages logged into the user log file since last reboot or last time the counter was cleared.

loggerUserLogNumError.name: loggerUserLogNumError
loggerUserLogNumError.description: Indicates the number of Error messages logged into the user log file since last reboot or last time the counter was cleared.

loggerUserLogNumFatal.name: loggerUserLogNumFatal
loggerUserLogNumFatal.description: Indicates the number of Fatal messages logged into the User-Log since last reboot or last time the counter was cleared.

loggerUserLogClearCountersTime.name: loggerUserLogClearCountersTime
loggerUserLogClearCountersTime.description: The time since user log counters were last cleared. Writing a 0 to this object causes the user log counters to be cleared.

subscribersInfoTable.name: subscribersInfoTable
subscribersInfoTable.description: The subscribers information table consists of data regarding subscribers management operations performed.

subscribersNumIntroduced.name: subscribersNumIntroduced
subscribersNumIntroduced.description: Indicates the current number of subscribers introduced to the SCE. These subscribers may or may not have IP address or VLAN mappings. Subscribers who do not have mappings of any kind cannot be associated with traffic, thus will be served by the SCE according to the default settings.

subscribersNumFree.name: subscribersNumFree
subscribersNumFree.description: Indicates the number of subscribers that may be introduced in addition to the subscribers that are already introduced to the SCE (subscribersNumIntroduced).

subscribersNumIpAddrMappings.name: subscribersNumIpAddrMappings
subscribersNumIpAddrMappings.description: Indicates the current number of 'IP address to subscriber' mappings.

subscribersNumIpAddrMappingsFree.name: subscribersNumIpAddrMappingsFree
subscribersNumIpAddrMappingsFree.description: Indicates the number of free 'IP address to subscriber' mappings that may be used for defining new mappings.

subscribersNumIpRangeMappings.name: subscribersNumIpRangeMappings
subscribersNumIpRangeMappings.description: Indicates the current number of 'IP-range to subscriber' mappings.

subscribersNumIpRangeMappingsFree.name: subscribersNumIpRangeMappingsFree
subscribersNumIpRangeMappingsFree.description: Indicates the number of free 'IP-range to subscriber' mappings that may be used for defining new mappings.

subscribersNumVlanMappings.name: subscribersNumVlanMappings
subscribersNumVlanMappings.description: Indicates the current number of VLAN to subscribers mappings.

subscribersNumVlanMappingsFree.name: subscribersNumVlanMappingsFree
subscribersNumVlanMappingsFree.description: Indicates the number of free 'VLAN to subscriber' mappings that may be used for defining new mappings.

subscribersNumActive.name: subscribersNumActive
subscribersNumActive.description: Indicates the current number of active subscribers, these subscribers necessarily have an IP address or VLAN mappings that define the traffic that should be associated and served according to the subscriber service agreement.

subscribersNumActivePeak.name: subscribersNumActivePeak
subscribersNumActivePeak.description: Indicates the peak value of subscribersNumActive since the last time it was cleared or the system started.

subscribersNumActivePeakTime.name: subscribersNumActivePeakTime
subscribersNumActivePeakTime.description: Indicates the time since the subscribersNumActivePeak value occurred.

subscribersNumUpdates.name: subscribersNumUpdates
subscribersNumUpdates.description: Indicates the accumulated number of subscribers database updates received by the SCE.

subscribersCountersClearTime.name: subscribersCountersClearTime
subscribersCountersClearTime.description: Indicates the time since the subscribers counters were cleared. Writing a 0 to this object causes the counters to be cleared.

subscribersNumTpIpRanges.name: subscribersNumTpIpRanges
subscribersNumTpIpRanges.description: Indicates the current number of 'Traffic Processor IP ranges' used.

subscribersNumTpIpRangesFree.name: subscribersNumTpIpRangesFree
subscribersNumTpIpRangesFree.description: Indicates the number of free 'Traffic Processor IP ranges'.

subscribersNumAnonymous.name: subscribersNumAnonymous
subscribersNumAnonymous.description: Indicates the current number of anonymous subscribers.

subscribersNumWithSessions.name: subscribersNumWithSessions
subscribersNumWithSessions.description: Indicates the current number of subscribers with open sessions.

tpInfoTable.name: tpInfoTable
tpInfoTable.description: The Traffic Processor Info table consists of data regarding traffic handled by the traffic processors by classification of packets and flows.

tpModuleIndex.name: tpModuleIndex
tpModuleIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies the module where this traffic processor is located.

tpIndex.name: tpIndex
tpIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies this traffic processor within a module. The value is determined by the location of the traffic processor on the module. Valid entries are 1 to the value of moduleNumTrafficProcessors for this module.

tpTotalNumHandledPackets.name: tpTotalNumHandledPackets
tpTotalNumHandledPackets.description: Indicates the accumulated number of packets handled by this traffic processor since last reboot or last time this counter was cleared.

tpTotalNumHandledFlows.name: tpTotalNumHandledFlows
tpTotalNumHandledFlows.description: Indicates the accumulated number of flows handled by this traffic Processor since last reboot or last time this counter was cleared.

tpNumActiveFlows.name: tpNumActiveFlows
tpNumActiveFlows.description: Indicates the number of flows currently being handled by this traffic processor.

tpNumActiveFlowsPeak.name: tpNumActiveFlowsPeak
tpNumActiveFlowsPeak.description: Indicates the peak value of tpNumActiveFlows since the last time it was cleared or the system started.

tpNumActiveFlowsPeakTime.name: tpNumActiveFlowsPeakTime
tpNumActiveFlowsPeakTime.description: Indicates the time since the tpNumActiveFlowsPeak value occurred.

tpNumTcpActiveFlows.name: tpNumTcpActiveFlows
tpNumTcpActiveFlows.description: Indicates the number of TCP flows currently being handled by this traffic processor.

tpNumTcpActiveFlowsPeak.name: tpNumTcpActiveFlowsPeak
tpNumTcpActiveFlowsPeak.description: Indicates the peak value of tpNumTcpActiveFlows since the last time it was cleared or the system started.

tpNumTcpActiveFlowsPeakTime.name: tpNumTcpActiveFlowsPeakTime
tpNumTcpActiveFlowsPeakTime.description: Indicates the time since the tpNumTcpActiveFlowsPeak value occurred.

tpNumUdpActiveFlows.name: tpNumUdpActiveFlows
tpNumUdpActiveFlows.description: Indicates the number of UDP flows currently being handled by this traffic processor.

tpNumUdpActiveFlowsPeak.name: tpNumUdpActiveFlowsPeak
tpNumUdpActiveFlowsPeak.description: Indicates the peak value of tpNumUdpActiveFlows since the last time it was cleared or the system started.

tpNumUdpActiveFlowsPeakTime.name: tpNumUdpActiveFlowsPeakTime
tpNumUdpActiveFlowsPeakTime.description: Indicates the time since the tpNumUdpActiveFlowsPeak value occurred.

tpNumNonTcpUdpActiveFlows.name: tpNumNonTcpUdpActiveFlows
tpNumNonTcpUdpActiveFlows.description: Indicates the number of non TCP/UDP flows currently being handled by this traffic processor.

tpNumNonTcpUdpActiveFlowsPeak.name: tpNumNonTcpUdpActiveFlowsPeak
tpNumNonTcpUdpActiveFlowsPeak.description: Indicates the peak value of tpNumNonTcpUdpActiveFlows since the last time it was cleared or the system started.

tpNumNonTcpUdpActiveFlowsPeakTime.name: tpNumNonTcpUdpActiveFlowsPeakTime
tpNumNonTcpUdpActiveFlowsPeakTime.description: Indicates the time since the tpNumNonTcpUdpActiveFlowsPeak value occurred.

tpTotalNumBlockedPackets.name: tpTotalNumBlockedPackets
tpTotalNumBlockedPackets.description: Indicates the accumulated number of packets discarded by this traffic processor according to application blocking rules.

tpTotalNumBlockedFlows.name: tpTotalNumBlockedFlows
tpTotalNumBlockedFlows.description: Indicates the accumulated number of flows discarded by this traffic processor according to application blocking rules.

tpTotalNumDiscardedPacketsDueToBwLimit.name: tpTotalNumDiscardedPacketsDueToBwLimit
tpTotalNumDiscardedPacketsDueToBwLimit.description: Indicates the accumulated number of packets discarded by this traffic processor due to subscriber bandwidth limitations.

tpTotalNumWredDiscardedPackets.name: tpTotalNumWredDiscardedPackets
tpTotalNumWredDiscardedPackets.description: Indicates the accumulated number of packets discarded by this traffic processor due to congestion in the queues.

tpTotalNumFragments.name: tpTotalNumFragments
tpTotalNumFragments.description: Indicates the accumulated number of fragmented packets handled by this traffic processor.

tpTotalNumNonIpPackets.name: tpTotalNumNonIpPackets
tpTotalNumNonIpPackets.description: Indicates the accumulated number of non IP packets handled by this traffic processor.

tpTotalNumIpCrcErrPackets.name: tpTotalNumIpCrcErrPackets
tpTotalNumIpCrcErrPackets.description: Indicates the accumulated number of packets with IP CRC error handled by this traffic processor.

tpTotalNumIpLengthErrPackets.name: tpTotalNumIpLengthErrPackets
tpTotalNumIpLengthErrPackets.description: Indicates the accumulated number of packets with IP length error handled by this traffic processor.

tpTotalNumIpBroadcastPackets.name: tpTotalNumIpBroadcastPackets
tpTotalNumIpBroadcastPackets.description: Indicates the accumulated number of IP broadcast packets handled by this traffic processor.

tpTotalNumTtlErrPackets.name: tpTotalNumTtlErrPackets
tpTotalNumTtlErrPackets.description: Indicates the accumulated number of packets with TTL error handled by this traffic processor.

tpTotalNumTcpUdpCrcErrPackets.name: tpTotalNumTcpUdpCrcErrPackets
tpTotalNumTcpUdpCrcErrPackets.description: Indicates the accumulated number of TCP/UDP packets with CRC error handled by this traffic processor.

tpClearCountersTime.name: tpClearCountersTime
tpClearCountersTime.description: Indicates the time since the traffic processor statistics counters were last cleared. Writing a 0 to this object causes the traffic processor counters to be cleared.

tpHandledPacketsRate.name: tpHandledPacketsRate
tpHandledPacketsRate.description: Indicates the rate in packets per second of the packets handled by this traffic processor.

tpHandledPacketsRatePeak.name: tpHandledPacketsRatePeak
tpHandledPacketsRatePeak.description: Indicates the peak value of tpHandledPacketsRate since the last time it was cleared or the system started.

tpHandledPacketsRatePeakTime.name: tpHandledPacketsRatePeakTime
tpHandledPacketsRatePeakTime.description: Indicates the time since the tpHandledPacketsRatePeak value occurred.

tpHandledFlowsRate.name: tpHandledFlowsRate
tpHandledFlowsRate.description: Indicates the rate in flows opening per second of the flows handled by this traffic processor.

tpHandledFlowsRatePeak.name: tpHandledFlowsRatePeak
tpHandledFlowsRatePeak.description: Indicates the peak value of tpHandledFlowsRate since the last time it was cleared or the system started.

tpHandledFlowsRatePeakTime.name: tpHandledFlowsRatePeakTime
tpHandledFlowsRatePeakTime.description: Indicates the time since the tpHandledFlowsRatePeakTime value occurred.

tpCpuUtilization.name: tpCpuUtilization
tpCpuUtilization.description: Indicates the percentage of CPU utilization, updated once every 2 minutes.

tpCpuUtilizationPeak.name: tpCpuUtilizationPeak
tpCpuUtilizationPeak.description: Indicates the peak value of tpCpuUtilization since the last time it was cleared or the system started.

tpCpuUtilizationPeakTime.name: tpCpuUtilizationPeakTime
tpCpuUtilizationPeakTime.description: Indicates the time since the tpCpuUtilizationPeak value occurred.

tpFlowsCapacityUtilization.name: tpFlowsCapacityUtilization
tpFlowsCapacityUtilization.description: Indicates the percentage of flows capacity utilization.

tpFlowsCapacityUtilizationPeak.name: tpFlowsCapacityUtilizationPeak
tpFlowsCapacityUtilizationPeak.description: Indicates the peak value of tpFlowsCapacityUtilization since the last time it was cleared or the system started.

tpFlowsCapacityUtilizationPeakTime.name: tpFlowsCapacityUtilizationPeakTime
tpFlowsCapacityUtilizationPeakTime.description: Indicates the time since the tpFlowsCapacityUtilizationPeak value occurred.

tpServiceLoss.name: tpServiceLoss
tpServiceLoss.description: Indicates the relative amount of service loss in this traffic Processor, in units of 0.001%, since last reboot or last time this counter was cleared.

pportTable.name: pportTable
pportTable.description: A list of port entries. The number of entries is determined by the number of modules in the chassis and the number of ports on each module.

pportEntry.name: pportEntry
pportEntry.description: Entry containing information for a particular port on a module.

pportModuleIndex.name: pportModuleIndex
pportModuleIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies the module where this port is located.

pportIndex.name: pportIndex
pportIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies this port within a module. The value is determined by the location of the port on the module. Valid entries are 1 to the value of moduleNumPorts for this module.

pportType.name: pportType
pportType.description: The type of physical layer medium dependent interface on the port.

pportNumTxQueues.name: pportNumTxQueues
pportNumTxQueues.description: The number of transmit queues supported by this port.

pportIfIndex.name: pportIfIndex
pportIfIndex.description: The value of the instance of the ifIndex object, defined in MIB-II, for this port.

pportAdminSpeed.name: pportAdminSpeed
pportAdminSpeed.description: The desired speed of the port. The current operational speed of the port can be determined from ifSpeed.

pportAdminDuplex.name: pportAdminDuplex
pportAdminDuplex.description: The desired duplex of the port.

pportOperDuplex.name: pportOperDuplex
pportOperDuplex.description: Indicates whether the port is operating in half-duplex or full-duplex.

pportLinkIndex.name: pportLinkIndex
pportLinkIndex.description: Indicates the linkIndex of the link that this port belongs to. Value of 0 indicates that this port is not associated with any link. Value of -1 indicates that this port is associated to multiple links.

pportOperStatus.name: pportOperStatus
pportOperStatus.description: Indicates the status of the port and if the port is down indicates the reason.

txQueuesTable.name: txQueuesTable
txQueuesTable.description: This table consists of information on the SCE's transmit queues.

txQueuesModuleIndex.name: txQueuesModuleIndex
txQueuesModuleIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies the module where this queue is located.

txQueuesPortIndex.name: txQueuesPortIndex
txQueuesPortIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies the port where this queue is located.

txQueuesQueueIndex.name: txQueuesQueueIndex
txQueuesQueueIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies this queue within a port. The value is determined by the location of the queue on the port. Valid entries are 1 to the value of portNumTxQueues for this module.

txQueuesBandwidth.name: txQueuesBandwidth
txQueuesBandwidth.description: The bandwidth in L1 kbps configured for this queue.

txQueuesUtilization.name: txQueuesUtilization
txQueuesUtilization.description: The percentage of bandwidth utilization relative to the configured rate.

txQueuesUtilizationPeak.name: txQueuesUtilizationPeak
txQueuesUtilizationPeak.description: Indicates the peak value of txQueuesUtilization since the last time it was cleared or the system started.

txQueuesUtilizationPeakTime.name: txQueuesUtilizationPeakTime
txQueuesUtilizationPeakTime.description: Indicates the time since the txQueuesUtilizationPeak value occurred.

txQueuesClearCountersTime.name: txQueuesClearCountersTime
txQueuesClearCountersTime.description: Indicates the time since the TX queues statistics counters were last cleared. Writing a 0 to this object causes the TX queues counters to be cleared.

txQueuesDroppedBytes.name: txQueuesDroppedBytes
txQueuesDroppedBytes.description: Amount of dropped L3 bytes. This is valid only if the system is configured to count dropped bytes per TX queue.

globalControllersTable.name: globalControllersTable
globalControllersTable.description: This table consists of information on the SCE's Global Controllers. note: the globalControllersIndex and the SCE CLI configuration index have a offset of one i.e. 1 in the MIB refers to 0 in the CLI.

globalControllersModuleIndex.name: globalControllersModuleIndex
globalControllersModuleIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies the module where this controller is located.

globalControllersPortIndex.name: globalControllersPortIndex
globalControllersPortIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies the port where this controller is located.

globalControllersIndex.name: globalControllersIndex
globalControllersIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies this controller within a port.

globalControllersBandwidth.name: globalControllersBandwidth
globalControllersBandwidth.description: The L1 bandwidth configured for this controller.

globalControllersUtilization.name: globalControllersUtilization
globalControllersUtilization.description: The percentage of bandwidth utilization relative to the configured rate.

globalControllersUtilizationPeak.name: globalControllersUtilizationPeak
globalControllersUtilizationPeak.description: Indicates the peak value of globalControllersUtilization since the last time it was cleared or the system started.

globalControllersUtilizationPeakTime.name: globalControllersUtilizationPeakTime
globalControllersUtilizationPeakTime.description: Indicates the time since the globalControllersUtilizationPeak value occurred.

globalControllersClearCountersTime.name: globalControllersClearCountersTime
globalControllersClearCountersTime.description: Indicates the time since the controllers statistics counters were last cleared. Writing a 0 to this object causes the controllers counters to be cleared.

globalControllersDroppedBytes.name: globalControllersDroppedBytes
globalControllersDroppedBytes.description: Amount of L3 dropped bytes. This is valid only if the system is configured to count dropped bytes per global controller.

appInfoTable.name: appInfoTable
appInfoTable.description: This table consists of information on the SCE's application.

appPropertiesTable.name: appPropertiesTable
appPropertiesTable.description: The application properties table provides the list of properties available for the application. The table is cleared when the application is unloaded.

apIndex.name: apIndex
apIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identify the property.

apName.name: apName
apName.description: Application property name. Property can be either scalar or array type.

appPropertiesValueTable.name: appPropertiesValueTable
appPropertiesValueTable.description: The applications properties value table is used to provide specific values for the applications properties. An entry must be created by setting the entry's apvRowStatus object with createAndGo (4) before setting the name of the property requested. To specify the property set the apvPropertyName objects. The apvPropertyName must be one of the properties from the appPropertiesTable. To remove an entry set the apvRowStatus object with destroy (6). To poll the application property, poll the apvPropertyStringValue, apvPropertyUintValue, or apvPropertyCounter64Value object. The table is cleared when the application is unloaded.

apvPropertyName.name: apvPropertyName
apvPropertyName.description: A name that uniquely identifies the application property. Array type properties may be accessed each element at a time in C like format, e.g. x[1], or y[1][2].

apvRowStatus.name: apvRowStatus
apvRowStatus.description: This object controls creation of a table entry.

apvPropertyStringValue.name: apvPropertyStringValue
apvPropertyStringValue.description: The value of the application property in display string format.

apvPropertyUintValue.name: apvPropertyUintValue
apvPropertyUintValue.description: The value of the application property in unsigned integer. If the property can't be casted to unsigned integer this object returns zero.

apvPropertyCounter64Value.name: apvPropertyCounter64Value
apvPropertyCounter64Value.description: The value of the application property in Counter64 format. If the property can't be casted to Counter64, getting this object returns zero.

subscribersPropertiesTable.name: subscribersPropertiesTable
subscribersPropertiesTable.description: The subscribers properties table provides the list of properties available for each subscriber.

spIndex.name: spIndex
spIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identify the property.

spType.name: spType
spType.description: Subscriber application property type in respect to: variable type (integer, boolean, string etc), number of elements (scalar or array) and restrictions if any exist.

subscribersPropertiesValueTable.name: subscribersPropertiesValueTable
subscribersPropertiesValueTable.description: The subscribers properties value table is used to provide subscriber properties values for subscribers introduced into the SCE. An entry must be created by setting the entry's spvRowStatus object with createAndGo (4) before setting any other of the entry's objects. To specify the subscriber's property set the spvSubName and spvPropertyName objects. The spvPropertyName must be one of the properties from the subscribersPropertiesTable. To remove an entry set the spvRowStatus object with destroy (6). To poll the subscriber property the manager need to poll the spvPropertyStringValue, the spvPropertyUintValue or the spvPropertyCounter64Value objects. The table is cleared when the application is unloaded.

spvSubName.name: spvSubName
spvSubName.description: A name that uniquely identifies the subscriber.

spvPropertyName.name: spvPropertyName
spvPropertyName.description: A name that uniquely identifies the subscriber property. Array type properties may be accessed each element at a time in C like format, e.g. x[1], or y[1][2].

spvRowStatus.name: spvRowStatus
spvRowStatus.description: This object controls creation of a table entry. Only setting the createAndGo (4) and destroy (6) will change the status of the entry.

spvPropertyStringValue.name: spvPropertyStringValue
spvPropertyStringValue.description: The value of the subscriber property in string format.

spvPropertyUintValue.name: spvPropertyUintValue
spvPropertyUintValue.description: The value of the subscriber property in unsigned integer. If the property can't be casted to unsigned integer this object returns zero.

spvPropertyCounter64Value.name: spvPropertyCounter64Value
spvPropertyCounter64Value.description: The value of the subscriber property in Counter64. If the property can't be casted to Counter64 this object returns zero.

trafficCountersTable.name: trafficCountersTable
trafficCountersTable.description: The Traffic counters table provides information regarding the value of different the traffic counters.

trafficCountersEntry.name: trafficCountersEntry
trafficCountersEntry.description: Entry containing information about a traffic counter.

trafficCounterIndex.name: trafficCounterIndex
trafficCounterIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies the counter.

trafficCounterName.name: trafficCounterName
trafficCounterName.description: The name given to this counter.

trafficCounterType.name: trafficCounterType
trafficCounterType.description: Defines whether there the traffic counters counts by 'packets(3)' or by 'bytes(2)'.

attackTypeTable.name: attackTypeTable
attackTypeTable.description: The Attack type table provides information regarding detected attacks, aggregated by attack type.

attackTypeEntry.name: attackTypeEntry
attackTypeEntry.description: Entry containing aggregated information about attacks of a given type.

attackTypeIndex.name: attackTypeIndex
attackTypeIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies the attack type.

attackTypeName.name: attackTypeName
attackTypeName.description: The name of this attack type.

attackTypeCurrentNumAttacks.name: attackTypeCurrentNumAttacks
attackTypeCurrentNumAttacks.description: The current amount of attacks detected of this type.

attackTypeTotalNumAttacks.name: attackTypeTotalNumAttacks
attackTypeTotalNumAttacks.description: The total amount of attacks detected of this type since last clear.

attackTypeTotalNumFlows.name: attackTypeTotalNumFlows
attackTypeTotalNumFlows.description: The total amount of flows in attacks detected of this type since last clear.

attackTypeTotalNumSeconds.name: attackTypeTotalNumSeconds
attackTypeTotalNumSeconds.description: The total duration of attacks detected of this type since last clear.

vasServerTable.name: vasServerTable
vasServerTable.description: The VAS server Table provides information on each VAS server operational status.

vasServerEntry.name: vasServerEntry
vasServerEntry.description: Entry containing information about VAS server status.

vasServerIndex.name: vasServerIndex
vasServerIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a VAS server.

vasServerId.name: vasServerId
vasServerId.description: The ID of the VAS server.

vasServerAdminStatus.name: vasServerAdminStatus
vasServerAdminStatus.description: Indicates only the administrative status of the VAS sever, in order to activate a server it should be also configured with a VLAN and a group.

vasServerOperStatus.name: vasServerOperStatus
vasServerOperStatus.description: Indicates the operational status of the VAS sever.

mplsVpnSoftwareCountersTable.name: mplsVpnSoftwareCountersTable
mplsVpnSoftwareCountersTable.description: The MPLS VPN software counters table provides information on various system software counters related to MPLS VPN auto learn.

mplsVpnSoftwareCountersEntry.name: mplsVpnSoftwareCountersEntry
mplsVpnSoftwareCountersEntry.description: Entry containing information about MPLS VPN auto learn SW counters.

mplsVpnMaxHWMappings.name: mplsVpnMaxHWMappings
mplsVpnMaxHWMappings.description: The maximum number of MPLS VPN mappings supported by HW (including all kinds of mappings).

mplsVpnCurrentHWMappings.name: mplsVpnCurrentHWMappings
mplsVpnCurrentHWMappings.description: The current number of HW MPLS VPN mappings in use.

operationalStatusOperationalTrap.name: operationalStatusOperationalTrap
operationalStatusOperationalTrap.description: OperationalStatusOperational notification signifies that the agent entity has detected the sysOperationalStatus object in this MIB has changed to 'operational(3)'.

operationalStatusWarningTrap.name: operationalStatusWarningTrap
operationalStatusWarningTrap.description: OperationalStatusWarning notification signifies that the agent entity has detected the sysOperationalStatus object in this MIB has changed to 'warning(4)'.

operationalStatusFailureTrap.name: operationalStatusFailureTrap
operationalStatusFailureTrap.description: OperationalStatusFailure notification signifies that the agent entity has detected the sysOperationalStatus object in this MIB has changed to 'failure(5)'.

systemResetTrap.name: systemResetTrap
systemResetTrap.description: A systemReset notification signifies that the agent entity is about to reset itself either per user's request or due to a fatal event.

chassisTempAlarmOnTrap.name: chassisTempAlarmOnTrap
chassisTempAlarmOnTrap.description: A chassisTempAlarmOn notification signifies that the agent entity has detected the chassisTempAlarm object in this MIB has changed to the 'on(3)' state (temperature is too high).

chassisTempAlarmOffTrap.name: chassisTempAlarmOffTrap
chassisTempAlarmOffTrap.description: A chassisTempAlarmOff notification signifies that the agent entity has detected the chassisTempAlarm object in this MIB has changed to the 'off(2)' state (temperature level is back to normal).

chassisVoltageAlarmOnTrap.name: chassisVoltageAlarmOnTrap
chassisVoltageAlarmOnTrap.description: A chassisVoltageAlarmOn notification signifies that the agent entity has detected the chassisVoltageAlarm object in this MIB has changed to the 'on(3)' state (voltage level is too high).

chassisFansAlarmOnTrap.name: chassisFansAlarmOnTrap
chassisFansAlarmOnTrap.description: A chassisFanStatusFailure notification signifies that the agent entity has detected the chassisFansAlarm object in this MIB has changed to the 'on(3)' state.

chassisPowerSupplyAlarmOnTrap.name: chassisPowerSupplyAlarmOnTrap
chassisPowerSupplyAlarmOnTrap.description: A chassisPsuStatusFailure notification signifies that the agent entity has detected the chassisPowerSupplyAlarm object in this MIB has changed to the 'on(3)' state.

rdrActiveConnectionTrap.name: rdrActiveConnectionTrap
rdrActiveConnectionTrap.description: RdrConnectionDestTypeActive notification signifies that the agent entity has detected the rdrFormatterDestStatus object in this MIB has changed to the 'active(2)' state.

rdrNoActiveConnectionTrap.name: rdrNoActiveConnectionTrap
rdrNoActiveConnectionTrap.description: A rdrNoActiveConnection notification signifies that the agent entity has detected there is no active connection between the RDR-formatter and any Data Collector.

rdrConnectionUpTrap.name: rdrConnectionUpTrap
rdrConnectionUpTrap.description: RdrConnectionStatusUp notification signifies that the agent entity has detected the rdrFormatterDestConnectionStatus object in this MIB has changed to 'up(2)'.

rdrConnectionDownTrap.name: rdrConnectionDownTrap
rdrConnectionDownTrap.description: RdrConnectionStatusDown notification signifies that the agent entity has detected the rdrFormatterDestConnectionStatus object in this MIB has changed to 'down(3)'.

telnetSessionStartedTrap.name: telnetSessionStartedTrap
telnetSessionStartedTrap.description: Replaced by the more generic sessionStartedTrap.

telnetSessionEndedTrap.name: telnetSessionEndedTrap
telnetSessionEndedTrap.description: Replaced by the more generic sessionEndedTrap.

telnetSessionDeniedAccessTrap.name: telnetSessionDeniedAccessTrap
telnetSessionDeniedAccessTrap.description: Replaced by the more generic sessionDeniedAccessTrap.

telnetSessionBadLoginTrap.name: telnetSessionBadLoginTrap
telnetSessionBadLoginTrap.description: Replaced by the more generic sessionBadLoginTrap.

loggerUserLogIsFullTrap.name: loggerUserLogIsFullTrap
loggerUserLogIsFullTrap.description: A loggerUserLogIsFull notification signifies that the agent entity has detected the User log file is full. In such case the agent entity rolls to the next file.

sntpClockDriftWarnTrap.name: sntpClockDriftWarnTrap
sntpClockDriftWarnTrap.description: An sntpClockDriftWarn notification signifies that the entity's SNTP agent did not receive time update for a long period, this may cause a time drift.

linkModeBypassTrap.name: linkModeBypassTrap
linkModeBypassTrap.description: A linkModeBypass notification signifies that the agent entity has detected that the linkOperMode object in this MIB has changed to 'bypass(2)'.

linkModeForwardingTrap.name: linkModeForwardingTrap
linkModeForwardingTrap.description: A linkModeForwarding notification signifies that the agent entity has detected that the linkOperMode object in this MIB has changed to 'forwarding(3)'.

linkModeCutoffTrap.name: linkModeCutoffTrap
linkModeCutoffTrap.description: A linkModeCutoff notification signifies that the agent entity has detected that the linkOperMode object in this MIB has changed to 'cutoff(4)'.

pcubeSeEventGenericString1.name: pcubeSeEventGenericString1
pcubeSeEventGenericString1.description: Temporary string used for traps. Always returns an empty string.

pcubeSeEventGenericString2.name: pcubeSeEventGenericString2
pcubeSeEventGenericString2.description: Temporary string used for traps. Always returns an empty string.

moduleAttackFilterActivatedTrap.name: moduleAttackFilterActivatedTrap
moduleAttackFilterActivatedTrap.description: A moduleAttackFilterActivated notification signifies that the agent entity's attack filter module has activated a filter. The pcubeSeEventGenericString1 is the type of attack-filter, which was activated.

moduleAttackFilterDeactivatedTrap.name: moduleAttackFilterDeactivatedTrap
moduleAttackFilterDeactivatedTrap.description: A portAttackFilterDeactivated notification signifies that the agent entity's attack filter module has removed a filter that was previously activated. The pcubeSeEventGenericString1 is the attack-filter type, which was sent in the corresponding moduleAttackFilterActivatedTrap. the pcubeSeEventGenericString2 is the reason for deactivating the filter.

moduleEmAgentGenericTrap.name: moduleEmAgentGenericTrap
moduleEmAgentGenericTrap.description: A generic notification used by the P-Cube EM agent. pcubeSeEventGenericString1 specifies what notification is it, and pcubeSeEventGenericString2 is the relevant parameter.

linkModeSniffingTrap.name: linkModeSniffingTrap
linkModeSniffingTrap.description: A linkModeSniffing notification signifies that the agent entity has detected that the linkOperMode object in this MIB has changed to 'sniffing(5)'.

moduleRedundancyReadyTrap.name: moduleRedundancyReadyTrap
moduleRedundancyReadyTrap.description: A moduleRedundancyReady notification signifies that the module was able to connect and synchronize with a redundant entity, and is now ready to handle fail-over if needed.

moduleRedundantConfigurationMismatchTrap.name: moduleRedundantConfigurationMismatchTrap
moduleRedundantConfigurationMismatchTrap.description: A moduleRedundantConfigurationMismatch notification signifies that the module was not able to synchronize with a redundant entity, due to a essential configuration parameters that are do not match between the module and the redundant entity.

moduleLostRedundancyTrap.name: moduleLostRedundancyTrap
moduleLostRedundancyTrap.description: A moduleLostRedundancy notification signifies that the module has lost the ability to perform the fail-over procedure.

moduleSmConnectionDownTrap.name: moduleSmConnectionDownTrap
moduleSmConnectionDownTrap.description: A moduleSmConnectionDown notification signifies that the module's virtual connection to the subscriber manager is broken.

moduleSmConnectionUpTrap.name: moduleSmConnectionUpTrap
moduleSmConnectionUpTrap.description: A moduleSmConnectionUp notification signifies that the module's virtual connection to the subscriber manager is up and working.

moduleOperStatusChangeTrap.name: moduleOperStatusChangeTrap
moduleOperStatusChangeTrap.description: A moduleOperStatusChangeTrap notification signifies that the moduleOperStatus has changed its value.

portOperStatusChangeTrap.name: portOperStatusChangeTrap
portOperStatusChangeTrap.description: A portOperStatusChangeTrap notification signifies that the portOperStatus object of the portIndex has changed its value, i.e., the link was forced down or the force down was released.

chassisLineFeedAlarmOnTrap.name: chassisLineFeedAlarmOnTrap
chassisLineFeedAlarmOnTrap.description: A chassisLineFeedAlarmOn notification signifies that the agent entity has detected the chassisLineFeed object in this MIB has changed to the 'on(3)' state.

rdrFormatterCategoryDiscardingReportsTra.name: rdrFormatterCategoryDiscardingReportsTrap
rdrFormatterCategoryDiscardingReportsTra.description: rdrCategoryDiscardingReportsTrap notification signifies that the agent entity has detected that reports send to this category are being discarded. The rdrFormatterCategoryNumReportsDiscarded object in this MIB is counting the amount of discarded reports.

rdrFormatterCategoryStoppedDiscardingRep.name: rdrFormatterCategoryStoppedDiscardingReportsTrap
rdrFormatterCategoryStoppedDiscardingRep.description: rdrCategoryStoppedDiscardingReportsTrap notification signifies that the agent entity has detected that reports send to this category are not being discarded any more. The rdrFormatterCategoryNumReportsDiscarded object in this MIB is counting the amount of discarded reports.

sessionStartedTrap.name: sessionStartedTrap
sessionStartedTrap.description: A sessionStarted notification signifies that the agent entity has accepted a new session. The pcubeSeEventGenericString1 is the session type (telnet/SSH) and client IP address.

sessionEndedTrap.name: sessionEndedTrap
sessionEndedTrap.description: A sessionEnded notification signifies that the agent entity has detected end of a session. The pcubeSeEventGenericString1 is the session type (telnet/SSH) and client IP address.

sessionDeniedAccessTrap.name: sessionDeniedAccessTrap
sessionDeniedAccessTrap.description: A sessionDeniedAccess notification signifies that the agent entity has refused a session from unauthorized source. The pcubeSeEventGenericString1 is the session type (telnet/SSH) and client IP address.

sessionBadLoginTrap.name: sessionBadLoginTrap
sessionBadLoginTrap.description: A sessionBadLogin notification signifies that the agent entity has detected attempt to login with a wrong password. The pcubeSeEventGenericString1 is the session type (telnet/SSH) and client IP address.

illegalSubscriberMappingTrap.name: illegalSubscriberMappingTrap
illegalSubscriberMappingTrap.description: A illegalSubscriberMappingTrap notification signifies that some external entity has attempted to create illegal or inconsistent subscriber mappings. The pcubeSeEventGenericString1 contains a message describing the problem.

loggerLineAttackLogFullTrap.name: loggerLineAttackLogFullTrap
loggerLineAttackLogFullTrap.description: Signifies that the agent entity has detected the line-attack log file is full. In such case the agent entity rolls to the next file.

vasServerOpertionalStatusChangeTrap.name: vasServerOpertionalStatusChangeTrap
vasServerOpertionalStatusChangeTrap.description: Signifies that the agent entity has detected that the vas server operational status has changed.

pullRequestNumber.name: pullRequestNumber
pullRequestNumber.description: Used only for traps to signify the number of pull requests issued so far for the anonymous subscriber given in the pullRequestRetryFailedTrap containing notification. A direct get will always returns 0.

pullRequestRetryFailedTrap.name: pullRequestRetryFailedTrap
pullRequestRetryFailedTrap.description: Signifies that an unknown subscriber wasn't identified after a certain number of pull requests. The value of pcubeSeEventGenericString1 is the subscriber id and the pullRequestNumber is the number of pull requests made on this sub.

mplsVpnTotalHWMappingsThresholdExceededT.name: mplsVpnTotalHWMappingsThresholdExceededTrap
mplsVpnTotalHWMappingsThresholdExceededT.description: Sent when the value of mplsVpnCurrentHWMappings exceeds the allowed threshold.

pcubeCompliance.name: pcubeCompliance
pcubeCompliance.description: A compliance statement defined in this MIB module, for SCE SNMP agents. with old deprectated groups. This compliance includes deprecated groups.

pcubeComplianceRev1.name: pcubeComplianceRev1
pcubeComplianceRev1.description: A compliance statement defined in this MIB module, for SCE SNMP agents.

pcubeMplsVpnAutoLearnGroup.name: pcubeMplsVpnAutoLearnGroup
pcubeMplsVpnAutoLearnGroup.description: MPLS VPN auto learning related information.
